deck: Attorney, gun rights activist, mutant-for-a-day.
description:
Origin

Antjie was an attorney that fought for stricter gun control. Unbeknownst to her, she was injected with a serum that turned her into a mutant.

Creation

Written by Simon Spurrier and drawn by Jorge Molina.

Major Story Arcs

It had been arranged that Antjie would speak at the Security and Defense Symposium. The committee learned, however, that Antjie had recently become a mutant, something she had also just barely found out. She begins speaking at the symposium anyway until music fills her ears. The music is a code that ignites the serum. Her body explodes and kills 3,000 people. This event is dubbed the Alexandria Incident.
name: Antjie Qoboza

deck: leader of the Knight Shift
description:
Taser was the leader of the Knight Shift, the mutant guards of the Institution of Doc 30, a sadic scientist who experimented in young metahumans and twist them as his personal army. After being broken and manipulated Taser became into one of the most cruelest warden of the Institution and rose to warden commander.

This would end when Ferro, a previous inmate and unofficial member of the time traveling Legion of Superheroes from century 31st went to rescue his brother Douglas. When the Knight Shift threatened with kill his brother, a desperate Douglas, provoked a riot among the prisioner, who take advantage and killed the guards, including Taser.

Taser was inspired in Cyclops from the X-men, even had a mirror relationship with fellow teammate Psych.
name: Taser

deck: Member of the Knight Shift and girlfriend of Taser.
description:
Psych was one of the members of the Knight Shift, prisoners manipulated to become warden of a prision for young metahumans under the control of Doc 30, who experimented on them. She also fell when the prisioners from the instalation escaped.

Because his mental powers and his relationship with Taser, is clear than Psych was a homage/parody for the X-woman Jean Grey.
name: Psych

deck: The wildcard of the Knight Shift.
description: Fangg was one of the many members of the Knight Shift. A wild and uncontrolable beast with a bloodlust and cybernetic claws than must be always chained to obey orders. He was killed when the prisioners of the institution of Doc 30 escaped.
name: Fangg

deck: Member of the Knight Shift.
description:
Landslide was a member of tha Knight Shift and a mutant prisioner of the Doc 30 Institution. He became a cynic cruel warden after years of torture. He used his powers to torture their fellow prisioners.

When Ferro and his brother Ingot caused a massive escape from the cells, the prisioners take brutal revenge on Landslide and his companions for years of torture .

Landslide was created to mimic the image of Iceman, his direct inspiration.
name: Landslide

When Ferro went to save his brother, the situation ended in a prisioners revolt. Kritter didn't survive to the inmates revenge.

Kritter was a pastiche of Colossus.

deck:
Although often mistaken as an Archie Andrews clone, Wilbur Wilkin debuted in "Zip Comics" #18 in September, 1941, actually predating Archie by three months, and is considered Archie Comics' first successful teen character. Though not as well known as Archie is today, Wilbur had his own series that ran for 15 years. 
In the late 60's Archie Comics' reused Wilbur's last name, Wilkin for the character, Bingo Wilkin, in "That Wilkin Boy". 
Other than sharing last names, they bear no likeness to one another.
name: Wilbur Wilkin
